ZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4/9/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4:04:20 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://homepage.dave-world.net/~ronin/maulsig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Buying and selling</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">my rant:<br>
<br>
I absolutely HATE people who dont know how to buy or sell in this game. Or those who arent willing to haggle a little for an item. <br>
<br>
Ex: Player 1 auctions &quot;Super helm for sale send tells!&quot; (ie pp not a super rare item/or trade only - its regularly sold)<br>
     You tell Player 1 &quot;how much?<br>
     Player 1 tells you &quot;make an offer&quot; (right here its annoying - you have to guess what they want)<br>
     You tell player 1 &quot;ill give you 175pp&quot;<br>
     Player 1 tells you &quot;nm thanks anyway&quot;<br>
How am I supposed to know what to offer if he doesnt haggle a little??? Does he REALLY need 200? Id probably go for that.. or is he thinkin 500?? I wont know unless he gives me an idea..<br>
<br>
Ex: You auction &quot;Great axe for sale tells!&quot;<br>
     Joe player tells you &quot; How much?&quot;<br>
     You tell him &quot; 200 or best offer&quot;<br>
     Joe player says &quot;no thanks thats too much...&quot;<br>
Did I just not say or best offer?? Make me an offer! Heck If you roleplay it out youll get a great deal! I just love when people haggle a little.. and offer me below my price.. I always tell em. &quot;HEY! I got 8 kids to feed! I got to have this much (price in between)&quot; I usually get less than what I want. but sometimes I get more. Just next time take a moment to follow up on a deal.. dont just say No thats too much and walk away.. not everyones prices are rock solid......<br>
<br>
</font><P><center>
