</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#F5F5DC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usarcoth.showPublicProfile>Sarcoth</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.sacredhaven.com/pics/avatar.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4/17/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>12:51:55 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Buying and selling</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I completely agree with both of you.  To be honest, sometimes when I hear someone auctioning an item I don't know, I'll ask them for the stats.<br>
<br>
Someone auctions, &quot;WTS Something.&quot;<br>
I tell Someone, &quot;What are the stats on Something?&quot;<br>
Someone tells me, &quot;Something + / +.&quot;<br>
I tell Someone, &quot;Sounds nice, what are you looking to get for it?&quot;<br>
Someone tells me, &quot;Make an offer.&quot;<br>
<br>
Um, how can I make a valid offer if I never even heard of it before?  So, then I go on to probably make some worthless offer to Someone and the same thing happens in Hokanu's example.<br>
<br>
And, I do agree with Degalus.  Other should keep quiet if they are not interested in the item.  If someone wants an item real bad, they are willing to pay whatever price they have to to get the item.  It's their call.  I've bought some things at high prices, but I don't have any regrets.  I learn from all trades, more and more each time.</font><P>Sarcoth Rashilon<BR>
